{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"e2b6879b-ee30-4a54-870a-2a0e562ee141","content":"The template looks well-structured but has a few issues before it's NuGet-ready:\n\n**Missing required field:**\n- `$schema` — recommended for validation (e.g., `\"$schema\": \"http://json.schemastore.org/template\"`)\n\n**Missing recommended fields:**\n- `\"preferNameDirectory\": true` — standard for project templates\n- `\"defaultName\"` — fallback project name if user doesn't specify one\n- `groupIdentity` / `precedence` — important if you plan multiple versions\n\n**Other concerns:**\n1. No `guids` array — if your template source has GUIDs (e.g., in `.csproj`/`launchSettings.json`), they won't be regenerated per instance.\n2. The `sourceName` replacement (`MyWebApi`) only works if your template content files actually use that literal string.\n\n**Verdict:** It's *functional* but not fully production-ready. At minimum, add the `$schema` property and consider `preferNameDirectory`/`defaultName`. Everything else (identity, shortName, author, tags, symbols) looks correct.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"009c00ff-d7ba-494e-ba97-cb9ea9eebb21","outputTokens":254,"requestId":"AC2C:13A49B:140BC0:18AA18:69F54B8E"},"id":"7628483e-af49-425b-8cb8-17b836b79ac9","timestamp":"2026-05-02T00:55:51.197Z","parentId":"dd3e3130-a69e-4ef8-ade9-438b5c62fcfc"}
